The paper focuses on machine learning and knowledge discovery, which are core topics in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the problem of selecting the best hypothesis from a feasible set, which is a common problem in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of algorithms for sampling and analyzing data suggests that the paper could also fit into the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper's focus on practical applications and experimental analysis could place it in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
